## What's going on in each version

### 🐛 Buggy Counter — the race condition
```
click fires  →  val = buggyCount   ← snapshot taken NOW
                     ↓
              setTimeout( () => buggyCount = val + 1 , 80ms )
```
If you click three times before any callback fires, **all three closures captured `val = 0`**. They each write `0 + 1 = 1`. Three clicks, count shows **1** — two updates are silently lost.

### ✅ Fixed Counter — the solution
```
click fires  →  setTimeout( () => {
                    current = fixedCount   ← read FRESH here
                    fixedCount = current + 1
                } , 80ms )
```
The read is deferred to the moment of execution. Callbacks run **sequentially** in the JS event loop, so each one sees the value written by the previous one. No updates are ever lost.

