```

### How to use it

1. **Save** the file as `race_condition_demo.html` and open it in any browser.
2. **Rapidly click `+1`** five or more times on the **Buggy** widget — watch the counter land on a value far lower than expected and notice the `⚠ CONFLICT!` warnings in the log.
3. Do the same on the **Fixed** widget — every click is counted correctly.

---

### Key concepts illustrated

| | Buggy | Fixed |
|---|---|---|
| **When count is read** | At dispatch time (synchronous, stale) | At resolution time (always fresh) |
| **Timers in-flight** | One per click | At most one at a time |
| **Lost updates** | Yes — concurrent callbacks overwrite each other | No — all deltas accumulate synchronously |
| **Pattern** | Read-Modify-Write with stale capture | Pending-delta queue + coalesced flush |

The root cause is the classic **stale-read race**: the buggy code captures `buggyCount` *before* the async delay, so every in-flight callback holds the same old value and the last writer wins. The fix moves the read to *after* the delay and ensures only one writer ever runs at a time, so no update is ever lost.

