<div class="explanation">
  <h2>📖 Why the Race Condition Happens &amp; How the Fix Works</h2>

  <div class="exp-grid">
    <div class="exp-card red">
      <h3>🐛 The Bug — Stale Closure Capture</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Click fires → current value of <code>count</code> is <strong>captured</strong> in the closure.</li>
        <li>A 200 ms <code>setTimeout</code> begins.</li>
        <li>While waiting, more clicks fire and capture the <em>same</em> stale value.</li>
        <li>All timers resolve and each writes <code>stale + 1</code>, overwriting each other.</li>
        <li>Result: 10 rapid clicks may only add 1–3 to the counter.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="exp-card green">
      <h3>✅ The Fix — Read at Write-Time</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Click fires → <strong>no value is captured</strong>; only a "pending increment" token is queued.</li>
        <li>When the timer resolves, it reads the <em>current live</em> <code>count</code> and adds 1.</li>
        <li>Because every callback reads fresh state just before writing, no two callbacks can overwrite each other.</li>
        <li>Result: 10 rapid clicks always add exactly 10.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Code comparison -->
  <pre>
<span class="cm">// ─── BUGGY version ────────────────────────────────────────────────</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> count = <span class="num">0</span>;

<span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">increment</span>() {
  <span class="bad">const captured = count;</span>          <span class="cm">// ← value frozen at click-time</span>
  <span class="fn">setTimeout</span>(() => {
    count = <span class="bad">captured</span> + <span class="num">1</span>;           <span class="cm">// ← writes stale + 1, overwrites other updates</span>
    render(count);
  }, <span class="num">200</span>);
}

<span class="cm">// ─── FIXED version ─────────────────────────────────────────────────</span>
<span class="kw">let</span> count = <span class="num">0</span>;

<span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">increment</span>() {
  <span class="cm">// nothing is captured — just schedule the work</span>
  <span class="fn">setTimeout</span>(() => {
    count = <span class="good">count</span> + <span class="num">1</span>;             <span class="cm">// ← reads live value at the moment of writing</span>
    render(count);
  }, <span class="num">200</span>);
}
