    </div>

    <div class="log-title">Operation Log</div>
    <div class="log" id="buggyLog"></div>

    <div class="timeline-title">Async Timeline (last ops)</div>
    <div class="timeline" id="buggyTimeline"></div>

    <div class="explain">
      <strong>The bug:</strong> <code>read → wait → write</code> is not atomic.
      If 5 clicks fire before any write completes, they all read <strong>the same value</strong>
      (e.g. 3), add 1, and all write back 4 — so 4 increments are silently <strong>lost</strong>.
      No error is thrown. The counter just lies.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ FIXED PANEL -->
  <div class="panel fixed">
    <div class="panel-title">✅ Fixed — Serialized Queue</div>
    <div class="panel-desc">
      Each increment is queued. The next op only starts after the
      previous write commits. No stale reads possible.
    </div>

    <div class="counter-box">
      <div class="counter-label">Counter Value</div>
      <div class="counter-value" id="fixedVal">0</div>
      <div class="expected-row">
        <span>Expected: <strong id="fixedExpected">0</strong></span>
        <span class="lost-label">Lost: <span class="lost-value zero" id="fixedLost">0</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="btn-row">
      <button class="btn-inc-fixed" onclick="fixedIncrement()">+1 (Queued)</button>
      <button class="btn-spam" onclick="spamClicks('fixed', 12)">💥 Spam ×12</button>
